{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readonly","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NSArray<MLNPolygon *>","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:Q$objc(cs)NSArray"},{"text":" * ","kind":"text"},{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The area occupied by any interior polygons is excluded from the overall shape."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Interior polygons should not overlap. An interior polygon should not have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interior polygons of its own."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If there are no interior polygons, the value of this property is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon(py)interiorPolygons","title":"interiorPolygons","fragments":[{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc: